UNJYNX - UX & Technical Research Report
========================================
Date: 2026-03-06
Scope: Onboarding, Projects, Settings, Profile, Offline Sync, WebSocket, Flutter Libraries

================================================================================
1. ONBOARDING SCREENS - BEST PRACTICES (2025-2026)
================================================================================

1.1 WHAT TOP APPS DO
---------------------

TODOIST:
- Redesigned onboarding in 2025 with fresh Welcome screen
- Profile screen moved EARLIER in flow (before workspace setup)
- Team workspace join available from the start (skip setup dance)
- First-time Browse tab shows guided tooltip
- Confetti animation on onboarding completion (delight moment)
- Progressive disclosure: core features first, advanced later

TICKTICK:
- Minimalist onboarding matching their subdued color theme
- Immediately shows value with built-in Pomodoro, habits, calendar
- Quick task creation demo during onboarding
- 25+ theme selection early in experience

THINGS 3:
- Ultra-clean, gesture-driven introduction
- Focuses on Areas > Projects > Tasks hierarchy
- Shows drag-and-drop, headings, and quick entry
- No account required (local-first) = zero friction start

NOTION:
- Role/use-case selection: "What will you use Notion for?"
- Template gallery shown during onboarding
- Workspace creation flow with team invites
- Progressive feature disclosure via tooltips

1.2 OPTIMAL NUMBER OF SCREENS
-------------------------------
Research consensus: 3-5 screens maximum, under 60 seconds total

Key statistics:
- 25% of users abandon after ONE use if value isn't clear immediately
- Reducing from 5+ to 3 screens significantly improves conversion
- Personalized onboarding paths increase completion by 35%
- Microlearning modules increase completion by 45%
- Maximum 4-7 personalization questions before overwhelming users

1.3 WHAT MAKES ONBOARDING GREAT IN 2026
-----------------------------------------

MUST-HAVE elements:
a) Value-first screen: Remind users WHY they downloaded (tagline + hero visual)
b) Personalization survey (2-3 questions max):
   - "What will you use UNJYNX for?" (work/personal/both/student/team)
   - "What's your biggest productivity challenge?" (forgetting tasks/too many apps/no routine)
   - "How do you want to be reminded?" (push/WhatsApp/Telegram/SMS)
c) Quick win: Create first task during onboarding (instant value)
d) Permission requests: Notifications, contacts - contextualized with WHY
e) Delight moment: Animation/confetti on completion

ANTI-PATTERNS to avoid:
- Feature tours that just list capabilities
- More than 5 screens before seeing the main app
- Forcing account creation before showing value
- Generic welcome without personalization
- Skip button that's hard to find

1.4 RECOMMENDED UNJYNX ONBOARDING FLOW (5 screens)
----------------------------------------------------
Screen 1: Hero splash - "Break the satisfactory. Unjynx your productivity." + Lottie animation
Screen 2: Use case selection - Work/Personal/Student/Team (cards with icons)
Screen 3: Reminder channel preference - Push/WhatsApp/Telegram/SMS/Email (multi-select)
Screen 4: Create your first task - Inline task creation with smart date parsing demo
Screen 5: Notification permission + "You're all set!" confetti celebration

Optional (post-onboarding): Tooltip overlays on main screen for first 3 sessions


================================================================================
2. PROJECT MANAGEMENT IN TODO APPS
================================================================================

2.1 ORGANIZATIONAL HIERARCHIES
-------------------------------

TODOIST structure:
  Folders > Sub-folders (2 levels) > Projects > Sections > Tasks > Sub-tasks
  - 13 theme color options for projects
  - Sections act as horizontal dividers within projects
  - Labels (tags) are global, cross-project
  - Filters: powerful custom views with boolean logic
  - Views: List view + Board (Kanban) view per project

TICKTICK structure:
  Folders > Lists > Sections > Tasks > Sub-tasks
  - 25+ themes + custom background images
  - Tags with color coding
  - Smart lists (auto-generated views: Today, Next 7 Days, All)
  - Multiple views: List, Kanban, Timeline, Calendar
  - Built-in Pomodoro timer per task
  - Habit tracking alongside tasks

THINGS 3 structure:
  Areas > Projects > Headings > Tasks > Checklists
  - Areas = broad life categories (Work, Personal, Health)
  - Projects = goal-oriented task collections within areas
  - Headings = visual dividers within projects (like sections)
  - Tags for cross-cutting categorization with Quick Find
  - Unique "When" scheduling: Today, Upcoming, Anytime, Someday
  - No kanban view - pure list-based, intentionally simple

2.2 UI PATTERNS
----------------

LIST VIEW (all three apps):
- Primary view, most used
- Task name, due date, priority indicator on each row
- Swipe actions (complete, schedule, delete)
- Drag-and-drop reordering
- Section/heading separators

BOARD/KANBAN VIEW (Todoist, TickTick):
- Columns based on sections, status, or custom grouping
- Cards show task name + metadata (due date, assignee, priority)
- Drag between columns to change status
- Todoist: any project can toggle between list and board
- TickTick: Kanban available for all lists

CALENDAR VIEW (TickTick):
- Monthly/weekly view with tasks on dates
- Drag tasks to reschedule
- Integration with external calendars

TIMELINE VIEW (TickTick):
- Gantt-chart style for project planning
- Shows task duration and dependencies

2.3 COLOR & ICON SYSTEMS
--------------------------
- Todoist: 19 project colors (Berry, Red, Orange, Yellow, Olive Green, Lime Green,
  Green, Mint Green, Teal, Sky Blue, Light Blue, Blue, Grape, Violet, Lavender,
  Magenta, Salmon, Charcoal, Grey)
- TickTick: Project colors + custom icon selection from icon library
- Things 3: Minimal color (mostly blue accent), no project colors/icons

RECOMMENDATION for UNJYNX:
- 20+ project colors (Material 3 palette, including midnight purple + gold brand colors)
- Icon picker from curated set (50-100 icons covering work, personal, health, finance, etc.)
- Emoji support as alternative to icons
- Custom color picker for Pro users

2.4 SORTING & GROUPING
------------------------
Common sort options across apps:
- Manual (drag and drop)
- Due date (ascending/descending)
- Priority (P1 > P2 > P3 > P4)
- Alphabetical
- Date added / Date modified
- Assignee (team features)

Grouping options:
- By section/heading
- By due date (Overdue, Today, Tomorrow, This Week, Later)
- By priority
- By label/tag
- By project (in "All" views)
- By assignee (team features)


